<p>An <b>e-mail address</b> identifies a location to which <a href="/wiki/E-mail" title="E-mail">e-mail</a> messages can be delivered. An e-mail address on the modern <a href="/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a> looks like, for example, <tt>jsmith@example.com</tt> and is usually read as "jsmith at example dot com". Many <a href="/wiki/E-mail#Origin" title="E-mail">earlier e-mail systems</a> had different formats for e-mail addresses and because modern e-mail systems are partially based on, and compatible with these older systems, the exact format of an e-mail address is complicated and frequently misunderstood.</p>
